OL,3,CTeenage soldier gave up dream job in
OL,4,Cthe army after being stabbed
OL,6,FDespite two years passing since Chris,
OL,7,Fwho is now 19, was stabbed, he is
OL,8,Fstill dealing with the consequences
OL,9,Ftoday.
OL,11,FAt the time, Chris was a young soldier
OL,12,Fwith a successful career ahead of him,
OL,13,Fbut he had to leave the army as a
OL,14,Fresult of the attack.
OL,16,F"I proved that I was fit enough to go
OL,17,Fback, but they didn't believe I was
OL,18,Fmentally fit to go back. They thought
OL,19,Fif I saw a knife or something that I
OL,20,Fcouldn't do it.
