OL,3,CTeenage soldier gave up dream job in
OL,4,Cthe army after being stabbed
OL,6,FIn response to the sentence, Chris
OL,7,Fsaid, "I feel angry about the boy who
OL,8,Falmost killed me, I'm happy that he
OL,9,Fgot nine years, but I hoped he got
OL,10,Fmore, but I'm happy with nine. I can
OL,11,Fmove on with my life now.
OL,13,FA Ministry of Justice spokesperson
OL,14,Fsaid: "This was an awful crime and
OL,15,Fwhile independent judges decide
OL,16,Fparticular sentences, our changes to
OL,17,Ftoughen up the law to punish knife-
OL,18,Fcarrying offenders has meant they are
OL,19,Ffar more likely to go to jail and for
OL,20,Flonger than ever before."
